    Jacquemin (1999) generates morphological, syntactic, and semantic variants for phrases in the agricultural domain.
    For example: Original: simultaneous measurements Variant: concurrent measures Original: development area Variant: area of growth Ravichandran and Hovy (2002) use semi-supervised learning to induce several paraphrastic patterns for each question type and use them in an open-domain question answering system.
